    <h2>FAQs</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>1. Are Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars gluten-free?</h3>
        <p>Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars are not certified gluten-free, and they are produced in facilities that also process gluten-containing ingredients. Therefore, they may not be safe for individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>2. Can individuals with gluten sensitivity consume Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars?</h3>
        <p>Individuals with mild gluten sensitivity may tolerate Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars, but those with celiac disease should avoid them due to the risk of cross-contamination.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>3. Are there any gluten-free alternatives to Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars?</h3>
        <p>Yes, there are several gluten-free snack bars available on the market. Look for products that are certified gluten-free to ensure they meet the necessary safety standards.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="conclusion">
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>While Nature Valley Sweet and Salty Bars do not contain gluten-containing ingredients, they are not certified gluten-free and are produced in facilities that process gluten. This makes them a risky choice for individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivity. For those who must avoid gluten, it is advisable to seek out certified gluten-free alternatives to ensure safety and peace of mind.</p>
